<P>APPLICATION COSTS (PP010)</P>
<P>This screen shows a summary of the payment records and costs for the 
particular application that you are in.</P>
<P>The summary window shows,</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE style="MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px">
  <P>Fee Type - Arrangement, valuation etc</P>
  <P>Total Amount Due</P>
  <P>Amount Outstanding</P>
  <P>Rebate/Addition - Any rebate or addition to the amounts</P>
  <P>Amount Paid</P>
  <P>Date of Payment</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>The options below this summary window enable you to process and amend the 
records and also add new ones if required.</P>
<P>Add Payment - This takes you to screen 'PP020 Add/Edit Payment'. From this 
option you can enter the details of the amount of a payment being made, the date 
of payment and also the method of payment from the dropdown box.</P>
<P>Edit Payment -</P>
<P>Delete Payment -</P>
<P>Rebate/Addition - This takes you to 'PP030 Adjust Fee Amount'. Here you are 
able to make an adjustment to the cost. You need to select whether it is a 
'Rebate' or an 'Addition', from the dropdown box named 'Adjustment'. In the 
field below it called, 'Amount', you need to insert the amount of the 
adjustment. If any notes need to be made about this, then there is space made 
available at the bottom of the screen.</P>
<P>Add New Fee Type - If you wish to add new costs/fees to the application, this 
screen which is, 'PP035 Add New Fee Type', is where it is done. You select the 
type of fee that you require from the dropdown box and enter the 'Amount Due' in 
the relevant field. If you select the option 'Other Fees', from the dropdown 
box, the field called, 'Other Fee' will be enabled and allow you to enter a 
description of those fees. Otherwise this field is NOT enabled. 
</P>             
                 
     
